ally and inferentially (including observation, care, recognition; and causatively, in"},{"code":"H3516","text":"through his liver","lemma":"כָּבֵד","translit":"","pos":"noun","disp":0,"lit":"liver","med":"liver","tho":"liver","range":"the liver (as the heaviest of the viscera)"},{"code":"H4116","text":"hasteth","lemma":"מָהַר","translit":"","pos":"verb","disp":0,"lit":"be carried headlong","med":"be carried headlong","tho":"fearful","range":"properly, to be liquid or flow easily, i.e. (by implication); to hurry (in a good or a bad sense); often used (with another verb) adverbially, promptly"},{"code":"H5315","text":"not that it is for his life","lemma":"נֶפֶשׁ","translit":"","pos":"adverb","disp":3,"lit":"soul","med":"soul","tho":"life/self","range":"properly, a breathing creature, i.e. animal of (abstractly) vitality; used very widely in a literal, accommodated or figurative sense (bodily or mental)"},{"code":"H6341","text":"to the snare","lemma":"פַּח","translit":"","pos":"noun","disp":0,"lit":"gin","med":"gin","tho":"snare","range":"a (metallic) sheet (as pounded thin); also a spring net (as spread out like a lamina)"},{"code":"H6398","text":"strike","lemma":"פָּלַח","translit":"","pos":"verb","disp":0,"lit":"bring forth","med":"bring forth","tho":"cleave","range":"to slice, i.e. break open or pierce"},{"code":"H6833","text":"as a bird","lemma":"צִפּוֹר","translit":"","pos":"noun","disp":0,"lit":"bird","med":"bird","tho":"fowl","range":"a little bird (as hopping)"}],"flags":[{"code":"H3045","lemma":"יָדַע","disp":2,"note":"Dispute level 2: multiple significant translation options."},{"code":"H5315","lemma":"נֶפֶשׁ","disp":3,"note":"נֶפֶשׁ — \"soul\" (Greek-influenced: non-material self) vs. \"life\" (the whole living person) vs. \"self\" (the person as subject). Hebrew nefesh is embodied, not a separate immaterial substance."}],"div":[{"code":"H2671","lemma":"חֵץ","lit":"arrow","tho":"dart"},{"code":"H3045","lemma":"יָדַע","lit":"know","tho":"know intimately"},{"